Reading existing resources with Data sources
---------------------------------------------

DATA BLOCK : 
Data blocks allow teraform to access info abt existing resources rather than creating new ones.

Access Existing Infrastructure
-------------------------------
Retrieve the details of existing resources so they can be transferred in other terraform blocks.

Dependency Resolution
----------------------
Data blocks help when one resource relies on the properties of another existing resource.

Avoid Hardcoding Values
-----------------------
Data blocks prevents the need for hardcoded values by dynamically pulling in details, which makes configurations more adaptable.

data "aws_vpc" "prd" {
  filter {
    name = "tag:Name"
    values = ["prd-vpc"]
  }
}
resource "aws_subnet" "pub" {
  vpc_id = data.aws_vpc.prd.id
  cidr_block = "10.0.0.1/24"
}
output "prd_vpc_subnet" {
  value = data.aws_vpc.prd.cidr_block
}

Referencing data blocks : data blocks retrieve a wide range of info abt the specified resource -called attributes.
Data block attributes are referenced just like resource attributes: data.<type>.<name>.<attribute>
      data.aws_vpc.prd.arn
      data.aws_vpc.prd.id
      data.aws_vpc.prd.cidr_block
      data.aws_vpc.prd.owner_id
      
